result.execSummary:
The defendant Josh M. Goff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Time served sentence.
Concurrent with: Waushara Co. Case No. 15CM327

15CM227, 15CM327 & 16CM26 Cases called @ 3:42 p.m. Defendant Josh M. Goff in court with attorney Andrew John Sulewski.  Defendant Josh M. Goff in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  16CM26 - Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. As to all cases:    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 15CM327: Cts 1 & 2 - NC. 16CM26: Ct 1 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 15CM227 - DRI. 16CM26: Ct 2 - DRI. No statement by DE. Court orders: 120 days WCJ as to each count concurrent - 90 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given.

ALSO INCLUDES CASE NOS. 15CM227 & 15CM327.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant and Atty Szilagyi appear via video from the WC Jail.

15CM227, 15CM327 & 16CM26 Cases called @ 1:01 p.m. Defendant Josh M. Goff in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 16CM26 - Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. ADA Anderson requesting $1000 Cash Bond. Atty Szilagyi takes no position as to bond. Court orders $1000 Cash Bond as to all cases.  IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for February 23, 2016 at 03:45 pm.
